STBLKeyStringList.Text: Aargh! Those greedy birds have {0.SimFirstName} feeling so ANGRY!

The melodious chirps of birds are always a nice pick-me-up...

Caw! Ca-caw!
Chaw! Chee-chaw!
A-coodle-doodle-do!
Coo-coo-ca-chaw!
Cluck! Cluck! Cluck-ahhh!
Around and around the flower goes, where it stops nobody knows!
Who knew a thin tarp and a little water is the difference between a nasty friction burn and a bunch of fun? That sliding was sublime!
The bubbles, they tickle! If {0.SimFirstName} gets tired of looking like a soapy yeti, {M0.he}{F0.she} can take a shower or change outfits to clear the suds away.
Ouch! That's going to leave a bruise on the behind... and perhaps an even bigger bruise to {0.SimFirstName}'s ego.
Flips, spins, and poses galore... {0.SimFirstName} has demonstrated {M0.his}{F0.her} prowess over the lawn water slide.
Oh no, was anyone watching?? That trick went spectacularly wrong...
Shaka-bra! That slide was siiiick bro!
Watching other Sims perform trick slides is nuts! {0.SimFirstName} is amped up!
That lawn water slide looks like a great time... maybe {0.SimFirstName} should get sliding!
Nothing wrong with taking pleasure in the failure of another Sim that attempted to showoff with a fancy trick slide. Serves 'em right!
Oooohhh OUCH! Wipeout! It's all fun and games when it isn't {0.SimFirstName} flopping on the lawn water slide.
Err... ouch! It hurt just watching that Sim wipeout on the lawn water slide.
If {0.SimFirstName} was taller, {M0.he'd}{F0.she'd} rip those wind chimes down when nobody was looking.
The melody of the wind chimes is like a massage for the mind.
If the wind could speak, it would do so through these lilting chimes, whose harmonious balance is an aural treat.
A classic white picket fence for your own little slice of suburbia! Unless you choose to paint it another color that is... in which case just ignore that first part.

This bird feeder is for the birds! ...err no, wait... it's so fowl it's foul! Ugh, that isn't right either... just remember to wipe away the bird poop every so often.\n\nAt the end of the day, just fill it with seed off and on and you'll treat yourself to the chirping melodies of local bluebirds, cardinals, and finches that are hungry for a nibble.
Enjoy arranging flowers? Then try positioning these floral decals on your home's walls. The possibilities are endless!
Feeling froggy? These colorful frog decals will cheer you right up! The vivid colors and busy patterns add eye-popping pop art to any setting.
A powdered drink mixture - just add water!

This is the perfect pitcher for mixing a thirst-quenching drink on a bright sunny day. Create lemonade, iced tea... even Citrus Swig (You remember their infamous jingle, right? ♪"Hot as a pig? Drink Citrus Swig!"♪) There's plenty to share, so gather your friends and kick back with a cold one.
These glasses fit perfectly on the Summer Drink Tray.
A classic white picket fence is only as welcoming as the gate that accompanies it. Well, look no further! Also available in other colors... but seriously, it's a picket fence.
Groovy, man. This far out light will light the path to your eternal illumination. Gaze into its depths and you just might get purple dazed.
This counterfeit candle may be a knockoff, but your guests will be none the wiser. Make it the centerpiece of your next backyard feast!
The lANTern is a fully functional ant deterrent device, that doubles as a heavy-duty lamp. Place it on your outdoor dining table and... presto! No ants; guaranteed.

Ah, the poor man's bug zapper. Experience freedom from cicadas (and other winged pests) with this rustic citronella. The extra-thick wick creates a sizable flame; ideal for lighting a patio after the sun goes down.

Have you ever taken a moment to think where light comes from? Sims think about it all the time. That's why they enjoy stringing these lights together to mimic the shape of their favorite constellations.
Let me wax lyrical about these wax paper prints: Stylish art, colors so fine, these gorgeous prints will blow your mind.
Step up your decorating game. This repurposed step-ladder makes the perfect perch for your potted perennials.
A pitcher for mixing drinks in.
This flowering Gumdrop plant is in full bloom! Observe its natural beauty... and don't you dare pot it.

Unapparent to the casual observer, these flowers aren't potted at all! In actuality, they're bouquet holders - for those times when you find yourself in desperate need of flowers. With three sizes to select from for any occasion, you can't go wrong!
Only the freshest live flowers come in this vibrant vase.

Is there a sadder sight than a potted Gumdrop plant? Scientists are baffled by the behavior they exhibit after being moved to a ceramic cage. Within days their flowers wilt and fall away, never to grow again.
Enjoy arranging flowers? Then try positioning these floral rugs on your home's floor. The possibilities are endless!
Feeling froggy? These colorful frog rugs will cheer you right up! The vivid colors and busy patterns add eye-popping pop art to any setting.

You'd think the Sun Rug would be round, but you'd be wrong. The name is derived from the synthetic threads used in the rug's stitching. When the sun reflects off it just so, it gleams with a blinding radiance.

Some plum actually sealed the opening to this birdhouse to prevent any birds from getting inside! What good is a birdhouse that can't house any birds? Placing it in your yard may raise a few eyebrows from the neighbors.
Spread your wings and fly... oh, if only. For now, this lawn ornament will have to be content accentuating the landscaping.
Hopefully your Sim is feeling better than this frog.
Everything you possibly need for a delicious backyard BBQ is thoughtfully stored away in the Completionist's Condiment Caddy...\n\n...wait a second, where's the mayonnaise!?
Pucker up buttercup; you'll want to have practiced your best pursed lips before you get a taste of the contents of this vase.

Take the classic folding chair design and remove the expensive metallic joints, and you're left with this practical seating! It may not collapse for easy storage, but you'll want to collapse into the comfortable patterned padding that's been amply added to the seat.
While the name of this chair is commonly thought to be a reference to its cushion, it's actually the chairback where the manufacturer drew inspiration from.
Can love bloom in the backyard? This sly fox certainly likes to think so. Let Hana Hal's Loveseat help set the mood.
It's adventure on the high seas! Conquer your fears and slide through the jaws of death... will you come out stronger on the other side?
AAAHH! Jaws of Death - Lawn Water Slide

Simple fun on a simple slide. That's what the Justa Lawn Water Slide promises, and that's what it delivers.\n\nJusta LLC is a limited liability corporation. Your usage of this product implies agreement that you will not hold Justa LLC liable for any injuries sustained when using the product responsibly... or otherwise.

Carbon dating on this boombox indicates it comes from hundreds of years... into the future?? Applying an electrical current to its circuitry causes the parts to amplify local radio waves and output their signal with crystal clarity. Some Sims speculate that this may be the head of an advanced cyborg... but that can't be possible, right?
A coffee table that helps inspire coffee talk? How novel! Creating small talk has never been simpler, as you marvel with others over the millefleurs pattern in the table's runner.
Dine out tonight... out in your backyard that is. A quick nosh will settle a rumbling tummy, allowing you time to appreciate the great outdoors.

With seating for up to six Sims, this large umbrella table is meant for entertaining! The umbrella material is made from a finely stitched together mesh that's ideal for looking out... or for looking down in.

Here's a nifty lifehack for the hungry Sim...\n\nWhile the Perfectly Patterned large umbrella table has room to seat six, you could only provide three chairs, thus doubling the available space for a Sim to serve themselves a meal. Makes perfect sense, right? Neat!

The Square Meals Dining Table proved so popular that the furniture factory ordered a second run. Unfortunately, a defect in the factory's tooling resulted in a dining table approximately two inches too short. Ever fastidious, the manufacturer refused to pass their problem along to you, and is instead offering this defective dining table as a fully functional end table!
This clever ensemble is comprised of a rugged patterned doormat draped over a solid wooden table. With such sturdy materials, it's shelving that's well suited for all your outdoor knick-knacks.
A funnel used to pour bird seed into the feeder.

Oh Windemere! When its musically gifted citizens aren't busy creating tourist videos for their sister city of Windenburg, they're honing their age-honored tradition of wind chime craftsmanship. Now you can bring the sound of Windemere into your own home!*

Choose from bamboo, ceramic, or metallic chimes.** Set the pitch of your chimes by changing the length of the rods. Mount them on your wall, or hang them from the ceiling.*** No matter if you have a single wind chime or group them together, you're sure to love the melodic notes wafting through your yard.

*AA Batteries included for indoor operation.
**Bamboo and aluminum chimes sold separately.
***Wall mounted wind chimes sold separately.
Wind Chimes of Windemere - Ceramic / Hanging

Gross! There aren't any fresh drinks to take from the tray.
This object must be placed outside to be filled with bird seed.
There are no birds feeding at this time.
Click on a Lawn Water Slide and select Trick Slide.
